Chuck Tanner, Pittsburgh Pirates Manager During '79 Title, Dies at Age 82

-- B y   J a y   B e b e r m a n
-- 
2011-02-11T21:53:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-11/chuck-tanner-pittsburgh-pirates-manager-during-79-title-dies-at-age-82.html
Chuck Tanner, who managed the
Pittsburgh Pirates to the 1979 World Series title, has died at
the age of 82, the Major League Baseball team said in a
statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jay Beberman at 
 jbeberman@bloomberg.net  